<subSubSection id="57C52D9FBC24D2E1971AA8A9749A1E00" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A675A2E5360312F9AC24D8BB57DD5195" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4608782198DC83F63CFF666162E1E286" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
<taxonomicName id="452E3D7FA9E92302262935ECDB0BEA0A" authorityName="Moreira &amp; Dumas &amp; Rozo &amp; Desidério &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Chimarra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata" subGenus="Chimarrita">Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="EBF793F9434845C054F4EAF662DBB120" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="ED2BFFD4ACDC160E12434089BECD970E" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. (Chimarrita) xingu" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xingu" subGenus="Chimarrita">C. (Chimarrita) xingu</taxonomicName>
Blahnik, 1997 by the short, fully divided tergum X with dorsal ridges and foldlike areas on outer margin of each lobe and the simple, almost uniform in width inferior appendages. However, the new species has an apically subtruncated ventral process of segment IX, while in 
<taxonomicName id="639F6A28FA7F164E8661B1355AA4798A" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. (Chimarrita) xingu" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xingu" subGenus="Chimarrita">C. (Chimarrita) xingu</taxonomicName>
this process is pointed. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="5B5E7050DC1D5D154D9FB9496B2A9F85" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. (Chimarrita) truncata" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata" subGenus="Chimarrita">C. (Chimarrita) truncata</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B73710CA9BB0D39A8618C674E9660DCC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">sp. nov.</emphasis>
can be recognized by inferior appendages with truncated apices both in lateral and ventral view (rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="3588AFA67EEE36CE204265C4391EB75F" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. xingu" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xingu">
<emphasis id="1BB3E5059F71DA3DEB4DD68C48940ABC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">C. xingu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6B910F2BA7FDBBF9BB1F541D1D64D61" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="description">
<paragraph id="5573730215B4D43E9693AA078DCD50C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1599898E01D1C4AEE5F8DECE5A0C8BC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="B62C52BA56EBE2AF577603A9A0D0B13E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Adult male</emphasis>
: forewing length 2.6-3.0 mm (n=6; holotype = 2.6 mm). General color (in alcohol) uniformly pale brown, except dorsum of the head dark brown, antennae and palps pale brown. Head with anterior, anteromesal, posterior, and posterolateral setal warts; posterior setal warts large, triangular, meeting broadly on median portion; postocular parietal sclerite triangular, slightly extending below eye. Maxillary palps relatively short, 2nd segment longer than 3rd segment, apicomesally with stout setae. Wing venation typical for the subgenus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C9EA12D2A19228CA48EB4EAAD097249F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype wing venation: A right forewing; B right hind wing. Abbreviations: DC, discoidal cell; MC, medial cell; TC, thyridial cell." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689953" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">3</figureCitation>
); forewing with forks I, II, III, and V present, stem of Rs straight, crossveins 
<emphasis id="06D3F6A161362B4D2301CAA413A67239" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">r</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="F94B558B3326B51BD67CCD4332F21434" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">s</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="D7896A8D767063E3CAB2ACB06B3E717B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">r-m</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="2F5C4F99742D299D5CBB85762EA65694" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">m</emphasis>
nearly linearly arranged and unpigmented, crossvein 
<emphasis id="AD6B43093F07CF28A84CA15C28048286" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">m-cu</emphasis>
and apex of Cu2 also hyaline; 2A apparently forked to 1A and 3A (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2A7DC30C4BFE5276D438985A58C4443B" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype wing venation: A right forewing; B right hind wing. Abbreviations: DC, discoidal cell; MC, medial cell; TC, thyridial cell." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689953" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">3A</figureCitation>
); hind wing venation not reduced, with forks I, II, III, and V present, Sc completely separated from R1; crossveins 
<emphasis id="8077D7523DBA40A2860694E7D5338EE9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">s</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="6615F54F7AE9FACF71393D50764F5E78" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">r-m</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B58447E6EF8B2ABA300AA3C8D39EBF00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">m-cu</emphasis>
unpigmented, crossvein between 1A and 2A (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0F74C753C8198A55B4CD475BFAA24CBA" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype wing venation: A right forewing; B right hind wing. Abbreviations: DC, discoidal cell; MC, medial cell; TC, thyridial cell." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689953" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">3B</figureCitation>
). Male protarsal claws nearly symmetrical; tibial spur formula 1-4-4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1457A930CE787E4AC4CA00BA4E68C16" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="32496FBEC33D3E571AA9E8B220BF0BC4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E16D7500A0FEAFF755B9D96ABC30DCE9" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4</figureCitation>
): Segment IX, dorsally with paired mesal and mesolateral ridges on each side of midline, mesal ones poorly developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="29A360206ED92F8E40DBCDA344A08FC6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4B</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, tall, with anterior margin concave, expanded anteroventrally and anterodorsally; posterolateral margin broadly convex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="98DFBECEEC556AA557B3612919448D92" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4A</figureCitation>
); ventral process moderately elongate, approximately 1/3 as long as inferior appendages, wider at basal half, slender at distal half, with subtruncate apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A2951E28684C9587A659E7B1616E5A52" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DBF4B4284783D01746E242BF332503D6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4C</figureCitation>
). Tergum X short, fused to segment IX; in dorsal view, fully divided mesally, forming 2 lobes with distinct sensilla foldlike area on outer margin, folding itself dorsally; apex of each lobe distinctly sclerotized, acute and slightly turned inwardly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BD5F19E46290F8B35D5581F8D9B6C544" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4B</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, strongly humped dorsally, apex short, slender, curved apicoventrally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="19D1F1E67B2CC8ACD4606A34F71FB0D1" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4A</figureCitation>
). Preanal appendages short, rounded, fused dorsolaterally near base of tergum X (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A35C9F908A944144E7877D6EE8D037E" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8FDC442C42293CDED82F3152E143A10F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4B</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages of moderate length, simple in structure, almost uniform in width in lateral and ventral views, apex truncate, with slightly irregular margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DE9A96F09CC8E799E9DEA6D98AA81890" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chimarra (Chimarrita) truncata sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D phallus, left lateral view; E phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689954" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">4A, C</figureCitation>
). Phallic apparatus with phallotheca tubular, bearing basodorsal and apicoventral pointed extensions; phallic spine single, stout, with moderate length, emerging dorsally near base of phallotheca; endotheca elongate, inflated dorsoapically; phallotremal sclerite complex indistinct (Fig. 
